{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χειμ-άζω</b> <br /> (<i>future</i> -άσω[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Signis Tempestatum” 38)\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>transitive</i>, <b>expose to the winter cold</b>: found only in <i>passive</i>, <b>to be exposed thereto,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης” 3.68 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>pass the winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 503; ὅπως χειμασθῇ καὶ ἡλιωθῇ ἡ γῆ 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.20.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of trees, <b>live through the winter,</b> χειμασθέντα [δένδρα] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “HP” 4.14.1; χειμασθῆναι χειμῶσι ὡραίοις καὶ καλοῖς [prev. author] “CP” 2.1.2. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>intransitive</i>, <b>pass the winter,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1097 (Lyric poetry), 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 5.9, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 7.54, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: of armies, <b>go into winter quarters,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.133, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.2.15, 3.2.1, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 27.18.1, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>raise a storm</b> or <b>tempest,</b> θεοῦ τοιαῦτα χειμάζοντος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1504; ὅταν χειμάζῃ ὁ θεὸς ἐν τῇ θαλάττῃ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 8.16, compare “IG” 7.4255.5 (Orop.); χειμάσει [ἡ νεφέλη] ἐφ᾽ ἡμᾶς 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.195d \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>impersonal</i>, ἐχείμαζε ἡμέρας τρεῖς <b>the storm continued,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.191 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χειμάσει <b>there will be stormy weather,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Sign.” [prev. cited] \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> with <i>accusative</i>, <b>drive forth</b> or <b>away,</b> of a storm, ἔξω χ. [τοὺς μύας] [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “fragment” 174.7 \">Refs</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be driven by a storm, overtaken by it,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.25, 3.69, +others; χειμασθεὶς ἀνέμῳ [prev. author] 8.99; ἐν θαλάττῃ χειμαζομένου πλοίου 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 540b, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>toss like a storm, distress,</b> τόδ᾽ αἷμα χ. πόλιν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 101; τὴν σάρκα τὸ παρὸν μόνον χειμάζειν 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Fragmenta” 452 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: also, <b>annoy, vex,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 331, 4th-3rd c.BC: Menander Comicus 208, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ παρρησίας” p.61 O., “POsl.” 48.8 (1st c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σφὴξ τοῖς κέντροις πλήσσων ἐχείμαζε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-4th c.BC: Aesopus Fabularum Scriptor 393 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:—<i>passive</i>, <b>to be tempest-tossed, distressed,</b> especially of the state considered as a ship, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 269, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 361; δόμων ὄλβος χειμάζεται 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 966 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of single persons, κατὰ θάλασσαν χειμασθεῖσαι (as example of a ψυχικὸν πάθος) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Soranus Medicus 3.84 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; <b>suffer grievously,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 563 (_anapaest meter_), 838, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 1460 (_anapaest meter_), 5th c.BC: Gorgias Rhetor et Sophista “Pal.” 11, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Politicus” 273d; ἰσχὺς ἐν νόσῳ χειμάζεται 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ichn.” 267; ταῖς σαῖς ἀπειλαῖς αἷς ἐχειμάσθην [prev. author] “Ant.” 391; ἄλλῃ δ᾽ ἐν τύχῃ χ. 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 315; χειμαζόμεθα.. ὑπ᾽ ἀπορίας ἐν τοῖς νῦν λόγοις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Philebus” 29b, compare “La.” 194c; ὑπό τινων “PSI” 4.349.4 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν στρατείαις ἢ νόσοις ἢ ἐν θαλάττῃ χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 170a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of feverish patients, χειμάζονται μάλιστα πεμπταῖοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “προγνωστικόν” 24. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5492","accentedUnicode":"χειμάζω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5494","matchingForm":"χειμών","stepTransliteration":"cheimōn","gloss":"winter","_zh_tw_Gloss":"冬天","_es_Gloss":"invierno","_zh_Gloss":"冬天"}],"shortDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to be batteredbatter in a storm","mediumDef":"(<i>passive</i>) to be batteredbatter in a storm <br /><b>to excite a tempest, toss with a tempest;</b>, <i>passive</i> <b>to be storm-tossed,</b> <ref='Act.27.18'>Acts 27:18</ref>*","stepGloss":"be storm-tossed","stepTransliteration":"cheimazō","count":1,"_es_Definition":"ser azotado por la tormenta, pasar por mal tiempo","_zh_tw_Definition":"在暴風雨中顛簸 (徒 27:18)","_zh_Definition":"在暴风雨中颠簸 (徒 27:18)","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"được đập/ được lắc trong một cơn bão.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"被風浪驅逼","_es_Gloss":"ser sacudidos por una tormenta","_zh_Gloss":"被风浪驱逼"}]}